    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: 'visibility' set to 'hidden'</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visufx.html#propdef-visibility" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="A block with 'visibiliy' set to 'collapse' will not be rendered on the page but will still affect layout flow." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                background: red;
                height: 100px;
                visibility: hidden;
                width: 100px;
            }
            #div2
            {
                background: black;
                height: 100px;
                width: 100px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is no red on the page and the box below is not directly adjacent to this text.</p>
        <div id="div1">FAIL FAIL</div>
        <div id="div2"></div>
